name: Old Head Golf Course
description: Located on a stunning peninsula in County Cork, Ireland, Old Head Golf Course offers breathtaking views of the Atlantic Ocean and a challenging links-style course. It combines natural beauty with a rich history, as golfers can experience holes set on cliffs that were once home to ancient fortresses. Prepare for an unforgettable golfing experience at Old Head Golf Course.

name: Pebble Beach Golf Course
description: Pebble Beach Golf Course is an iconic coastal masterpiece, renowned for its breathtaking beauty, challenging terrain, and unforgettable views.

name: Pinehurst #2
description: Pinehurst #2 is a historic and revered golf course, characterized by its timeless elegance, strategic design, and undulating fairways that demand precision and skill from players.

name: St Andrews' Old Course
description: The Old Course at St. Andrews is a legendary golfing destination steeped in rich history, where golfers from around the world are captivated by its ancient charm, iconic landmarks, and the test of links golf at its finest.

name: Lahinch Golf Club
description: Lahinch Golf Club is a captivating links course nestled along the rugged west coast of Ireland, celebrated for its natural beauty, thrilling dunes, and challenging layout that presents golfers with a true test of their skills and resilience.

name: Cabot Cliffs
description: Cabot Cliffs is a breathtaking golf course situated on the rugged cliffs of Cape Breton Island, Nova Scotia, offering golfers an awe-inspiring experience with its dramatic ocean vistas, undulating terrain, and world-class design that makes it a must-play destination for golf enthusiasts.

name: Old MacDonald
description: Old MacDonald Golf Course is a stunning tribute to the classic and timeless principles of golf course architecture, expertly designed to provide golfers with a harmonious blend of challenging play, natural beauty, and an unforgettable experience inspired by the game's origins.

name: Ailsa Turnberry
description: Turnberry Ailsa Golf Course is a majestic Scottish links gem, steeped in golfing history and set against a stunning coastal backdrop, where golfers are enchanted by its strategic challenges, lush fairways, and the undeniable allure of one of the world's most iconic golfing destinations.

name: Erin Hills
description: Erin Hills is a captivating championship golf course nestled in the rolling hills of Wisconsin, renowned for its sprawling layout, fescue-lined fairways, and firm, fast conditions that offer players a true test of skill and a memorable experience in the heartland of golf.

name: Bandon Trails
description: Bandon Trails is a picturesque golf course located amidst the stunning coastal landscape of Oregon, known for its seamless integration with the natural terrain, diverse layout, and challenging play that takes golfers on a journey through majestic forests and impressive dunes.

name: Prestwick
description: Prestwick Golf Club is a historic and revered Scottish links course, steeped in golfing heritage, where players are transported back in time to experience traditional golf, unique blind shots, and the charm of the game's origins, making it an unforgettable destination for golf enthusiasts.

name: River Blackwolf Run
description: River Blackwolf Run is a world-class golf destination located in Wisconsin, boasting two spectacular courses, The River and The Meadow Valleys, both designed by Pete Dye, where golfers are captivated by the challenging layouts, scenic landscapes, and a premier golfing experience that leaves a lasting impression.

name: Jubilee Course
description: The Jubilee Course is a historic and revered golf gem located at St. Andrews Links in Scotland, offering golfers an exhilarating coastal experience with its strategic design, undulating fairways, and stunning views of the North Sea, making it a cherished and must-play destination for golf enthusiasts.

name: Kiawah Island Ocean
description: Bandon Trails is a picturesque golf course located amidst the stunning coastal landscape of Oregon, known for its seamless integration with the natural terrain, diverse layout, and challenging play that takes golfers on a journey through majestic forests and impressive dunes.

name: Pinehurst #4
description: Pinehurst #4 is a premier golf course located in North Carolina's Pinehurst Resort, masterfully redesigned by Gil Hanse to blend classic golfing traditions with modern challenges, offering players a thrilling and rewarding experience amidst the stunning sandhills landscape.

name: Forest Dune
description: Pinehurst #4 is a premier golf course located in North Carolina's Pinehurst Resort, masterfully redesigned by Gil Hanse to blend classic golfing traditions with modern challenges, offering players a thrilling and rewarding experience amidst the stunning sandhills landscape.

name: Kingsbarns
description: Kingsbarns Golf Links is an exquisite golf course situated along the picturesque coastline of Scotland, near St. Andrews. Designed by Kyle Phillips, the course offers golfers a spectacular seaside layout, breathtaking views of the North Sea, and a challenging yet enjoyable golfing experience that has earned it a place among the top links courses in the world.

name: Bandon Dunes
description: Bandon Dunes Golf Resort is a world-renowned golf destination located in Oregon, USA. It features several stunning links-style courses, including Bandon Dunes, Pacific Dunes, Bandon Trails, Old Macdonald, and the newly added Sheep Ranch. Designed by notable architects like David McLay Kidd, Tom Doak, Bill Coore, and Ben Crenshaw, the resort offers golfers a true Scottish links experience, with rugged coastal landscapes, rolling dunes, and challenging play, making it a bucket-list destination for golf enthusiasts worldwide.

name: The Loop
description: The Loop is a unique and innovative golf course located at Forest Dunes Golf Club in Michigan, USA. Designed by Tom Doak, this one-of-a-kind reversible course allows golfers to play in two directions on the same layout, providing a fresh and challenging experience each time they tee it up, making it a must-visit destination for golfers seeking a new and exciting twist on traditional golf courses.

name: Pacific Dunes
description: Pacific Dunes is one of the spectacular links-style golf courses at Bandon Dunes Golf Resort in Oregon, USA. Designed by Tom Doak, it offers golfers a thrilling coastal experience with its dramatic ocean views, natural dunes, and strategic layout, creating an unforgettable golfing journey that perfectly captures the essence of traditional links golf and has earned it a place among the top-ranked courses in the world.
